text: Nizhniye Lemezy () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Lemezinsky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 707 as of 2010. There are 10 streets. == Geography == It is located 65 km from Iglino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District Category:Ufa Governorate
title: Nizhniye Lemezy
